annotation.TEXT: Yep, I expected that door to take me here, and fortunately, none of my functions are disabled in this room.
Not all that much.
Of course. Also, my buttons aren't disabled here. There must be a custom sprite at the beginning of the area that disables them.
MOOOONNN!!! HOW COULD YOU SEAL OFF A MOON?!?! YOU MONSTER!!!
I'm gonna want to come back here again and look for it...
Well, first, let me get my mushroom back since there's one right here.
The boneheads aren't cape-spinnable either.
Gotcha! Okay, now this next part looks like it would be a lot more difficult without the cape.
But, is there anything else in Barnyarn Mayhem that I have yet to check? And what about the fifth No P-switch coin in Switchless Castle? Find out next year! To be continued...
O... M... G! Let's hope Mario doesn't need to change his pants after that one!
Oh, man. It's an enlarged version of one of the Zelda 2 enemies. It looks like it's starting to melt the brown blocks below it, but it doesn't look like it'll break free in time to stop me!
Ah, Link's Awakening's Face Shrine music (I think it's from the southern shrine). Also, look at all those goodies! I really want that message box!
Alright, so spin jumping is disabled here, but what about flying?
That far. Wait, what? I can't try to turn around! The X button is disabled! Quick, Start+Select!
Hello, and welcome back to Barnyard Mayhem in TVW! There's a good reason why I'm back here...
More asymmetrical Roto-Discs, which both mess with my OCD and increase the difficulty. It's like the ultimate mind game... mind... game... mind... game...
And there's another off-center Roto-Disc. I'm guessing that was done intentionally.
Ah, but now that I've got a cape, and I managed to keep it with me to the end of the level (despite a few close calls), I've got some other things I want to check out!
Now, why would you go and disable the X button if you weren't also disabling Y?
No P-switches because they're allergic to mustard.
Umm... That Roto-Disc is not centered properly with its hub...
And... That's as far as I can go to the left. Oh, well. I do wonder if there is a secret up there that I missed... (If there is, let me know!)
Oh, man. That No P-switch coin looks really tricky to get.
Wow, that was way too dangerous!
Aha! Level broken! ...Oh, wait. I can't go any further. Maybe I could if I were to fly, but those Roto-Discs are so in the way...
Is there anything above that Thwomp (since he wasn't touching the ceiling)?
Yeah, can't cape spin that guy. Maybe I can make him despawn instead? ...Oh, cool, that worked.

Yep, and it sends you right back to the beginning of the mission. I do believe this is what all barns in this mission do (though I only checked a couple of them). Well, anyway, let's get out of here now.

YES!!! Ah, but that's not all. I was asked by wariolandgoldpiramid to see what's to the right of these turkeys in this level's second mission. This is probably going to hurt real bad, but here goes...
Wow, a 1000-Yoshi-coin piece?! Too bad I can't reach it, all because P-switches are allergic to mustard...
Oh, and I checked off camera, and none of those other buttons do anything. Only this one teleports you.
Whoa, I nearly hit my head on those spikes there.
Hey, I made it, and only took one hit. Not bad! However, there doesn't appear to be much over here. Does this barn act as a reset door at least?
Well, other than the main theme of teasing me with unreachable items, this seems like an ordinary castle level, which is fine.
Ah, this one does scroll up...
Alright, now I'd like to check to the right of this area, but getting the room to take off might be tricky...
No vertical scroll here, so I'm done with this place. What about Barnyard Mayhem? I'll just quickly check the mission select area...
Fortunately, that was the last part of that level that I wanted to check, so I'm done there. Next, I guess I'll make a quick check of Yoshi's House...
Is this level almost done yet?

Okay, now the voting results this time are as follows (despite me not holding a vote): 1 vote for Yoshi's House, 1 vote for TIME4 (see 4:52 of the previous episode), 1 vote for 0ver 9000-1 (sorry, but I can't count your vote 52 times), 1 vote for Mario to go eat a ham, 1 vote for me to try out create.swf on the Walfas blog and make a thing with it, 2 votes for 3-1, and 4 votes for Switchless Castle (including a vote for me to bring a switch in there, and a vote for me to bring a BFG9000 in there). Switchless Castle it is, then!
Can't fly over it. I guess it stretches up to effectively infinity. (Well, not that high, but high enough that it's impossible to get over since the screen doesn't scroll up.)
Wait, where's the fifth No P-switch coin?
The Skull Bro. and its skulls can be cape-thwacked though.
It's to brutally murder this green chicken! (Insert evil laughter here.)

O... M... G! The game just flat-out gives me a cape here?! Well, I know where I'm going after this level, assuming I don't lose the cape! (And, even if I do lose it, I'll just revisit this level for another one!)
Now, what's to the right of that button that warped me last time?
Whatever. I didn't need it.
Umm... Wow... I figured I'd be okay down there, but I still feel like that was a very risky move!
EEEEEEEEEEEEEEE!!!
Anyway, here's where midpoint starts you in this level.
I have no idea why this message is here. Maybe it's a hint about something, or maybe foreshadowing, but I don't know.
Gotta be careful with these donut blocks. Mmm... Donuts... (*drools*)
Those are some huge 1-ups...
Aw, man. I wanted to cape spin that Dry Bones... Maybe I can reach him through the wall?
Nope. I can fly perfectly fine!
The bats are not cape-spinnable, and I don't feel like checking if they're slide-killable (they're probably not). Now, as for this invisible wall...
Let's see where flying takes me here...
And, that's as far as I can go that way.
Oh, and now we've got some layer 2 shenanigans going on here...
Okay, this Tetris block should keep me safe for the moment. (I just can't get away from Tetris-related stuff lately, can I?)
I'm guessing that pipe is where you come out of if you enter this level at the midpoint entrance.
Plan? What plan? I never knew anything about this plan! What are you hiding from me?!
Aww... I can't enter that big red door, but that's okay. This normal door that's on the same screen should take me to the same place.
Haw, haw! Thwomps only land on the block that's below their left side.
Now, there was no invisible wall here, so how far does the screen scroll?
Okay, that's the first "No P-switch coin"...
Also, I can move freely on this screen, and I guess I have to stand in front of the door and press up to proceed.
And once again, there's nothing! Also, X is disabled here again, so I guess I gotta Start+Select.
